{"id": 5075, "title": "Ticket #5075: Many Core machines not detecting all cores on Windows", "description": "<blockquote>\nWe have a user with 24 Core Xeon E5-2690 running Windows were HTCondor is only detecting 12 of the 24 cores.\n\n<p>This is because in preparation for handling machines with &gt; 64 processors.  Microsoft has created a new concept called 'processor groups'.  They guarantee that the maximum number of processors in a processor group will always be less than 64 - But a program that calls <code>GetLogicalProcessorInformation</code> will only learn about processors in the same group as the thread making the call.  In order to find out about ALL processors, you must now call <code>GetLogicalProcessorInformationEx</code>. See this for more info.\n<a class=\"external\" href=\"https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/dd405503\">https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/dd405503</a></p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jul-02 13:06</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/d9d116cdfd5ea6124f3b2de275a13f7775e916eb\">[45203]</a></span>: update 8.2.9 version history items with edited versions of same items that come from the 8.3.6 and 8.3.7 versions, as release ordering caused replication of these items <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5114\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5114'); return false;\" title=\"job_dagman_abort-final-A consistently fails on Windows\">#5114</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?tic